rComments: Professor Bejan is probably one of the most passionate professors you'll come across. However, much of the information she presents is hard to grasp since there is so much of it and no lectures are posted online (need to attend lectures). The essays were hard but she gives ample extra credit opportunities that rise your grades.

I usually love political theory, but nearly dropped my entire POL major as a result of how disappointing this class was. Professor Bejan began the first class by telling us that she likes to make her students work hard and that it was going to be a hard year. Then she wrote a bunch of Latin on the board. She ruined political theory for me.

rComments: Extremely knowledgeable, passionate and enthusiastic about material, however lectures can be hard to follow at times. Tutorials & readings are curial, 7 books along with additional readings. Tough grading on essays, not fan of the exam format,  difficult to study for; to much information to grasp all at once. That being said, I did enjoy class.

When she presents, you can tell from the tone of her voice that she's very passionate and very well informed about her subject. She gives a lot of extra credit 14-15 15 extra credit throughout the year. Essay topics are hard, but interesting, then again it is Political Theory, so expect to read Plato, Aristotle, Machiavelli, etc. So fun.
